ptree_mod.c

1#include <linux/module.h>

2#include <linux/syscalls.h>

3//#include <linux/errno.h>

4#include <linux/sched.h>

5#include <linux/slab.h>

6#include <linux/list.h>

7#include <linux/uaccess.h>

8//#include <errno.h>

9

10MODULE_LICENSE("GPL v2");

11

12#define PTREE_SYSCALL_INDEX 398

13

14// For utilizing kernel symbols

15extern void* compat_sys_call_table[];

16extern rwlock_t tasklist_lock;

17

18struct prinfo {

19  int64_t state;            // current state of process

20  pid_t   pid;              // process id

21  pid_t   parent_pid;       // process id of parent

22  pid_t   first_child_pid;  // pid of oldest child

23  pid_t   next_sibling_pid; // pid of younger sibling

24  int64_t uid;              // user id of process owner

25  char    comm[64];         // name of program executed

26};

27

28void search(struct task_struct *task, struct prinfo *buf, int *nr_buf, int* nr_max) {

29    printk("-----search stage 1: %d %d-----\n", *nr_buf, *nr_max);

30    printk("addr task %p\naddr buf %p\naddr nr_buf %p\naddr nr_max %p", task, buf, nr_buf, nr_max);

31

32    if (*nr_buf < *nr_max) {

33        struct task_struct *curr_child;

34

35        printk("search stage 2\n");

36        printk("task->state: %lld\n", task->state);

37        buf[*nr_buf].state = task->state;

38        printk("buf[*nr_buf].state: %lld\n", buf[*nr_buf].state);

39

40        printk("task->real_cred->uid.val: %lld\n", task->real_cred->uid.val);

41        buf[*nr_buf].uid = task->real_cred->uid.val;

42        printk("buf[*nr_buf].uid: %lld", buf[*nr_buf].uid);

43        printk("search stage 3\n");

44

45        if (task->parent != NULL) {

46            buf[*nr_buf].parent_pid = task->parent->pid;

47        }

48

49        else {

50            buf[*nr_buf].parent_pid = 0;

51        }

52        printk("search stage 4\n");

53

54        if (list_empty(&(task->children))) {

55            printk("search stage 4.1\n");

56            buf[*nr_buf].first_child_pid = 0;

57            printk("search stage 4.2\n");

58        }

59

60        else {

61            printk("search stage 4.3\n");

62            buf[*nr_buf].first_child_pid = list_entry(&(task->children), struct task_struct, children)->pid;

63            printk("search stage 4.4\n");

64        }

65        printk("search stage 5\n");

66

67        if (list_empty(&(task->sibling))) {

68            printk("search stage 5.1\n");

69            buf[*nr_buf].next_sibling_pid = 0;

70            printk("search stage 5.2\n");

71        }

72

73        else {

74            printk("search stage 5.3\n");

75            buf[*nr_buf].next_sibling_pid = list_entry(&(task->sibling), struct task_struct, sibling)->pid;

76            printk("search stage 5.4\n");

77        }

78        printk("search stage 6\n");

79

80        // task->cred->uid, task->real_cred->uid, task->ptracer_cred->uid

81        // buf[*nr_buf].uid = (long)(task->real_cred->uid.val);

82        strncpy(buf[*nr_buf].comm, task->comm, 64);

83        printk("search stage 7\n");

84        buf[*nr_buf].pid = task->pid;

85        printk("search stage 8\n");

86    }

87

88    printk("search stage 8.1: %d\n", *nr_buf);

89    (*nr_buf)++;

90    printk("search stage 8.2: %d\n", *nr_buf);

91

92    struct task_struct* tmp;

93

94    list_for_each_entry(tmp, &(task->children), children) {

95        search(tmp, buf, nr_buf, nr_max);

96    }

97

98}

99

100int ptree(struct prinfo *buf, int *nr) {

101

102    printk("ptree stage 1\n");

103

104    if (!access_ok(VERIFY_READ, nr, sizeof(int))) {

105        // -EFAULT

106        return -11;

107    }

108

109    int nr_max;

110

111    printk("ptree stage 2\n");

112

113    get_user(nr_max, nr);

114

115    printk("ptree stage 3\n");

116

117    if (nr_max < 1) {

118        // -EINVAL

119        return -12;

120    }

121

122    if (!access_ok(VERIFY_READ, buf, sizeof(struct prinfo) * nr_max)) {

123        // -EFAULT

124        return -13;

125    }

126

127    printk("ptree stage 4\n");

128

129    struct prinfo *buf_buf = kmalloc(sizeof(struct prinfo) * nr_max, GFP_KERNEL);

130    printk("ptree stage 5\n");

131    int *nr_buf = kmalloc(sizeof(int), GFP_KERNEL);

132    printk("ptree stage 6\n");

133

134    copy_from_user(buf_buf, buf, sizeof(struct prinfo) * nr_max);

135    printk("ptree stage 7\n");

136

137    *nr_buf = 0;

138    

139    read_lock(&tasklist_lock);

140    printk("ptree stage 7.1\n");

141    search(&init_task, buf_buf, nr_buf, &nr_max);

142    printk("ptree stage 7.2\n");

143    read_unlock(&tasklist_lock);

144    printk("ptree stage 8\n");

145

146    copy_to_user(buf, buf_buf, sizeof(struct prinfo) * nr_max);

147    printk("ptree stage 9\n");

148    copy_to_user(nr, nr_buf, sizeof(int));

149    printk("ptree stage a\n");

150

151    int return_value = *nr_buf;

152

153    kfree(buf_buf);

154    printk("ptree stage b\n");

155    kfree(nr_buf);

156    printk("ptree stage c\n");

157

158    return return_value;

159}

160

161void* legacy_syscall = NULL;

162static int ptree_mod_init(void) {

163  // Reserve legacy syscall & replace it to yourown

164  printk("ptree_mod_init!\n");

165

166  legacy_syscall = compat_sys_call_table[PTREE_SYSCALL_INDEX];

167  compat_sys_call_table[PTREE_SYSCALL_INDEX] = ptree;

168

169  return 0;

170}

171

172static void ptree_mod_exit(void) {

173  // Revert syscall to legacy

174  printk("ptree_mod_exit!\n");

175

176  compat_sys_call_table[PTREE_SYSCALL_INDEX] = legacy_syscall;

177}

178

179module_init(ptree_mod_init);

180module_exit(ptree_mod_exit);
